BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:YJM51_LI7oWtNwQcVfFbY
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260314T154858Z
DTSTART:20260326T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Pioneer Park\n\nJoin us for an afternoon work party in Pionee r
	 Park. This beautiful habitat is being threatened by non-native weeds\, su
	ch as ivy and blackberry. Ivy plays a big role in local habitat destructi 
	on by pulling down trees\, shading out native plants\, and reducing biodiv
	ersity. Join in our efforts and help to create a healthier forest. \n\nA l
	l ages welcome\, and no experience necessary! Gloves\, tools\, water\, an 
	d small snacks provided.\n\nWhen: Thursday\, March 26th\, 4pm-6pm\n\nWhere
	: Pioneer Park SE\, Meet at the corner of Island Crest Way and SE 68th St.
	 Follow VOLUNTEER EVENT Signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in c
	loth es you don't mind getting dirty \\(think: long pants\, boots or sneak
	ers\\). Bring water. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools will be provided.\n
	\nRegistration: https://volunteersignup.org/CWRCR\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amc
	ity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer-park/18066420/2026-03-2
	6T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer
	-park/18066420/2026-03-26T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:92BjBStlzG1ZqaXg1efnU
SUMMARY:PACIFIC PLACE ‘SWEET SIXTEEN SHOWDOWN' WATCH PARTY FOR MARCH MADNES
	S FANS
DTSTAMP:20260314T154858Z
DTSTART:20260327T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:Pacific Place\, a premier five-story shopping center in downtow
	n Seattle \\(www.pacificplaceseattle.com\\)\, invites basketball fans to e
	xperience the excitement of the Sweet Sixteen round of the NCAA March Madn
	ess tournament during its “Sweet Sixteen Showdown” watch party from 5 p.m.
	 to 7 p.m. on Thursday\, March 26th. Guests can watch the games live on th
	e center’s brand-new 40-foot by 70-foot LED screen – capable of showing up
	 to three games simultaneously – before testing their skills at a basketba
	ll Pop-a-Shot challenge. The event will also feature a game-day pretzel ba
	r\, a cash bar serving signature cocktails\, and a basketball-themed photo
	 opportunity for fans to capture the moment. This event is free and open t
	o the public. While reservations are not required\, space is limited and g
	uests are encouraged to reserve a spot in advance at https://bit.ly/4b4q5Y
	k. To learn more\, click here or visit https://pacificplaceseattle.com/eve
	nts.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/pacific-place-sweet-
	sixteen-showdown-watch-party-for-march-madness-fans/18297298/2026-03-26T00
	\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/pacific-place-sweet-sixte
	en-showdown-watch-party-for-march-madness-fans/18297298/2026-03-26T00
LOCATION:PACIFIC PLACE\, 600 Pine Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
